Company Overview

We are Devoteam Portugal, a dynamic organization committed to delivering innovative solutions that captivate sports enthusiasts. Our mission is to push the boundaries of gaming and entertainment.

Salary

We offer an attractive annual salary of €80,000 to €120,000 depending on your level of experience and qualifications.

Job Description

We seek a seasoned Senior iOS Game Developer to join our team and help us craft immersive experiences that maximize the thrill of sports for our customers. As a key member of our development team, you will collaborate with cross-functional colleagues to design, develop, and deploy engaging products that exceed customer expectations.

Required Skills and Qualifications

To succeed in this role, you should have:
• A minimum of 4 years of experience in mobile game development (iOS), using Swift;
• Strong knowledge and experience in RESTful APIs;
• Experience with MVP and MVVM architectures;
• Experience with multi-threading and asynchronous logic;
• Experience in working in agile teams using Scrum;
• Nice-to-have: knowledge of Cocoa Touch and other Apple frameworks, experience with Git Flow, Jira, and Confluence.

Benefits

At Devoteam Portugal, we value diversity and inclusivity. We strive to create a work environment that fosters creativity, dynamism, and excellence. Our benefits package includes:
• An attractive salary range;
• Ongoing professional development opportunities;
• A supportive and collaborative team environment.

Others

We are an equal opportunities employer and welcome applications from candidates with disabilities. If you share our passion for innovation and excellence, please submit your application. We look forward to welcoming you to our team

Estamos com uma oportunidade para um dos nossos parceiros, uma empresa com projetos nacionais e internacionais e que está em um crescimento impressionante no mercado português e Europeu.

Venha fazer parte dessa equipa de sucesso
• *Requisitos**:

- Licenciatura em Informática ou similar;
- Inglês - B2;
- Conhecimentos sólidos de programação em IOS (Objective-C e/ou Swift);
- Capacidade de integração com serviços REST;
- Conhecimentos na escrita de testes unitários de acordo com as metodologias TDD e BDD;
- Ter conhecimento na Apple Human Interface Guidelines e capacidade para propor melhorias de usabilidade baseada nesta guideline;
- Experiência no desenvolvimento de projetos modulares;
- Experiência e boa adaptação a metodologias de desenvolvimento baseadas em Agile;
- Conhecimentos das frameworks UIKit e SwiftUI;
- Conhecimento das principais arquitecturas usas na plataforma (MVVM, MVC, VIPER);
- Duração: Contrato 12 Meses (possibilidade de prorrogação).
- Localização: Lisboa, híbrido (maioritariamente remoto).
• *Tipo de oferta**: Período Integral
